The paper deals with few-shot learning, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves learning a multi-level representation with a classifier-centric constraint, which is a technique used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper mentions the domain shift problem, which is a common issue in neural networks (cs.NE).
